The Brazilian Coffee Institute, IBC,plans to sell in a series of auctions over the next few weeksrobusta coffee purchased in London last year, but details ofwhere and when auctions will take place are still to befinalised, IBC president Jorio Dauster told reporters.    The sales of 630,000 bags of robusta and an unspecifiedamount of Brazilian arabica coffee will take place over aminimum of six months but it is not decided where sales willtake place or whether they will be held weekly or monthly.    The amount offered at each sale has also not been set, butcould be in the order of 100,000 bags, Dauster said. Reuter&#3;